The "if" statement is used for conditional execution in Python.
It allows you to execute a block of code only if a certain condition is true.

syntax:-

if Condition:
    Statement
else:
    Statement

--------------------------

elif:

if Condition:
    Statement
elif Condition:
    Statement
elif Condition:
    Statement
elif Condition:
    Statement
else:
    Statement

---------------------------

Nested if
if statements inside if statements, this is called nested if statements

if Condition:
    if Condition:
         Statement
    else:
         Statement
elif Condition:
    Statement
else:
   Statement

